channel.title: Barliegh Ranch Practice Day
channel.description: Well, since there's no racing tommorrow, My Dad, and the Owners of Barliegh Ranch Motocross Track and I decided to have a practice day for the riders. at the moment where I live it's quite cool today, it's a change from 40 degrees celcuis, so I hope it is like this tommorrow. I got a new neck protector yesterday so I'm alot comfortable on my bike, knowing that I can crash and have a bit more protection. It's going to be so fun/nailbiting, because I'm not the only one there, there's like 900 people there, all on bikes, some on 85's, some might even be on 525's. So I'm looking forward to it.They have a built a 30ft tripple that I might try tommorrow, bad thing is it's up hill, and my bike has no power compared to the big 450's and the big 525's.

The Un-Named:

What CC bike are you on? I had a little 50 CC and my friend had a 125, but damn, 525 is a lot of engine power.

I’m on a Yz85, just big wheel version, same horsepower, just bigger parts, and the wheels are bigger, thus being able to rev the bike to 15600rpm. I know my bike back to front :)[br][size=1]Posted at: December 02, 2006, 03:04:20 AM[/size][hr]And yes a 525 is kick-ass.

item.description:
@Yz85Racer wrote:

Well you get used to it. I always wear goggles You don’t feel it when you’re riding, just the sweat dripping down. But when you get off you fell so hot. I’m used to it cause that’s ow hot it is here all the time in Australia. So Yamaha Australia devoleped a padding that you put on your shoulders and neck, that has like frozen water in it, so when you get hot, it cools you down. I use one, I don’t know how I’d liv without one lol.
